13 / 15
Conclusion
1. From both theoretical and empirical studies in the US market, though both models perform
pretty well, FF5 dominants FF3.
FF5 explained average returns related to protability and investment that was left
unexplained by FF3.
FF5 has greater adjusted R
2
, suggesting that FF5 explains the excess returns better.
FF5 also performs better in GRS test, and has lower average absolute value and
unexpained ratio.
2. However, when it comes to the Asia market, the performance of both FF3 and FF5 become
slightly worse. Also, FF3 is better than FF5 regarding some statistics.
The dierent results in these two market might due to the dierent market styles, but it needs
further investigation. Another implication is that we may need to modify the factors in order
to t dierent markets.
